      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, and honestly the \"spirit\" thing is a good North Star for the brand identity, but i actually have to sketch clothes here lol. if i'm looking at mood boards, what are the actual visual signifiers of that urban aesthetic? like, if i want someone to look at a piece and immediately think \"urban/street\" rather than \"preppy\" or \"mainstream,\" what kind of colors, silhouettes, or specific vibes am i looking for? help me narrow down the visual language.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
