      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The visual language of street style often leans into a mix of utilitarian, oversized silhouettes, and bold, sometimes deliberately clashing graphics. Think heavy-duty fabrics, technical wear, and graphics that reference subcultures, not just mainstream trends. Color palettes frequently involve muted, industrial tones mixed with sudden, high-contrast pops of color, suggesting grit and energy. Ultimately, the vibe is about function meeting defiant self-expression, which is a very different energy than polished, preppy fashion.",
      "source": "target",
